Food companies buy mulberries from farmers in Zhenjiang, East China's Jiangsu Province, on Tuesday, when the mulberry purchasing period started. Zhenjiang is focused on mulberry cultivation and the area planted with the fruit is about 5,000 mu (333 hectares). A total of 100 tons of the fruit were sold on Tuesday alone. The selling period lasts for 20 to 30 days. Photo: VCG Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Utah celebrates 150th birthday of Transcontinental RailroadActress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame star